The paper deals with deep learning for image recognition tasks, specifically in the field of medical image computing. The focus is on volumetric data, which suggests a strong possibility of the paper belonging to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep residual learning and auto-context networks also suggests a likelihood of the paper belonging to the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the use of magnetic resonance (MR) images suggests a possibility of the paper belonging to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
